To help promote entrepreneurial skills development at the grassroots, Abuja Enterprise Agency (AEA) has commissioned its liaison office in Bwari Area Council. In a statement by the agency, the MD/CEO Muhammed Arabi Tukur, represented by the DGM Malam Shehu Abdulkadir, reiterated the agency’s commitment to Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs) development. “We will do everything within our capacity to make entrepreneurship known in every house hold within the area council,” he said. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Shehu also stated that the main intention of setting up the liaison office is to improve service delivery, provide business development services in the area councils and the expansion of the agency’s clientele base by bringing its services to the people at the grassroots. He listed some programmes and services the agency will be offering in the liaison office and urged the people of Bwari Area Council to take advantage of them to build their capacities. Chairman of Bwari Area Council Hon John Kabaya Shekeogaza thanked the agency for bringing the opportunity to his people and pledged his support to its progress. “We key into the entrepreneurship idea and believe that it will impact our people. With the support of the agency, our administration will get better,” the chairman said. AEA opens offices in area councils X-raying role of AEA in entrepreneurs’ growth in FCT AEA trains 800 youths, women in ICT, skills acquisition